<P><H1 align=center>ADD / EDIT EMPLOYMENT DETAILS – DC170</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>Employment Status: select the relevant status from the drop-down list to the 
right of the field. This includes employed, self-employed, retired, not employed 
etc.</P>
<P><H3>Employment Type: </H3>enter whether the applicant is 
employed on a permanent or temporary basis, or full or part time This 
information is required as there may be different ways of assessing the 
application based on whether the applicant is employed or self-employed (eg. if 
the applicant is self-employed, details of past accounts, projections, and 
further information about the company will be required, as an employer’s 
reference will not be applicable)
<P></P>
<P><H3>Employer / Trading Name: </H3>here the employer’s name 
(or trading name of company if self-employed) should be entered. If the name is 
stored in the directory, click on the Directory Search button to the right of 
the field – this brings up the Directory Search dialogue box (ZA020). Enter the 
company name and town and click the Directory Search button. If the employer is 
held in the directory, it will appear in the box below, and can be selected by 
highlighting the record and clicking ‘Select’
<P></P>
<P><H3>Industry / Occupation Type: </H3>these fields ask for 
clarification about the nature of the applicant’s employment (eg. industry type 
– education, finance, transport; occupation type – skilled, management, manual). 
Select the appropriate descriptions from the drop-down lists, then enter the job 
title in the next field, and the date started and left (if appropriate).
<P></P>
<P><H3>Address: </H3>if the company is listed in the 
directory, the address will carry over to DC170. If not, enter the postcode and 
click on ‘PAF Search’, which will bring up a list of addresses with that 
postcode. Select the relevant address and the address fields in DC170 will be 
populated. If the address is not found on PAF, it can be typed into the fields
<P></P>
<P><H3>Contact Details: </H3>enter the contact details for the 
person who would need to be contacted for an employment reference. This will be 
required to corroborate income and the permanency of the applicant’s job, which 
will be used in the overall assessment of the application
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads to the next 
screen.
